e. Wastes of wind-swept pasture\nland and lonely stretches of wooded\nlandscape receive a poetic and transform\ning touch in a quartet, of pictures which\nhang on the east wall, namely, \u201cDay's\nLast Gleam,\u2019\u2019 \u201cNovember Uplands,\u201d\n\u201cThe Tool of Twilight\u201d and \u201cThe Light\nBeypnd.\u201d Mr. Dyar. moreover, has\nseised eveyy opportunity tq render the\nvarious moods of nature, the storm, the\nsunset, the nightfall with its stillness and\ntho ocean in tell |ts majesty.\nRadically different In treatment is \u201cAn\nOld Norman Courtyard, shewing the\nold Normandy buildings and canal.\nWonderfully rich in lt\u00ab coloring\nof russet brown* and green* l* this pic\nture in which the artist ha* put so much\nof th* old mediaeval atjnosph*re and\nfeeling. \u201cThe Old House on the\nDelft\u201d and \u201cA Gorden of Yesterday\u201d are\nrecent pointing* toy the artist, full of rich\nand beautiful color. Tn tho marines on\nthe south wall one find* a strong sug\ngestion of Woodbury, the famous deep\nsea painter, in \u201cThe Rainy Bea-New\nport.\u201d \u201cThe Breakerw-Newport\u201d I* a\nsymphony in green and gray strongly\nsuggestive of WWitltf. Thia shows a\nstretch of oe**fo with the surf in the\nforeground. Other marine* are \u201cThe\nGray Sea\u2014Newport,\u201d \u201cwhere Sky and\nSea Are One,' 1 \u201cIn the Breakers\u201d and\n/\u2018A Lonesome Sea.\u201d\nOp the west wall one finds \u201cThe Old\nDutch Farm.\" exquisite Ip colpr and\ntreatment; also \u201cA Normandy Lane\u201d\nAa Amer loan Banker Abroad.\n(From the New Turk World.)\nThe crowned heads of Europe have ut\nall times shown themselves kindly dis\nposed toward American millionaires. They\nhave on numerous ouoaslona granted\nHudiences to visiting steel kings. But it\nhas bo*n left t<\u00bb J. Pierpont Morgan to\nreceive marks of royul favor of a kind\nnot usually a<\u2019Qorde<l to a commoner, tie\nmore than all the real is parsons grata in\npalaces. _\nIn London the Que